which could transport the Martyrs with fervent desires of being carried in fiery chariots of persecuting adversaries to Heaven, and administer no light to guide them upon Earth; and truth had wanted Champions, if some, like the Fox, who had lost his tail should not have perswaded beasts to a conformity to that which might deform them.
